                        <div class="slider-content">
                            <h3>Bandai Namco, the creator of Pac-Man, moves its HC in Orhideea Towers</h3>
                            <div class="date">August 17, 2018</div>
                            <div class="text-scroll mCustomScrollbar">
                                <p><strong>Bandai Namco Entertainment, active in mobile video platforms, the creator of Pac Man, leased 1,300 sqm in Orhideea Towers office building, developed by CA Immo, for its new headquarters.</strong></p>
                                <p>The process of selecting and renting the new 1.300 sqm space was coordinated by the Griffes real estate consultancy. The Orhideea Towers building, developed by CA Immo, was completed in early July 2018 near Grozavesti Metro Station. The two H-shaped towers include about 37,000 sqm of office space, already leased about 90 percent.</p>
                                <p>The two towers have 13 floors (GF + 12 floors), respectively 17 floors (GF 16 floors), with surfaces of up to 2,700 sqm per floor and two underground levels. The project includes 406 parking spaces and bicycle facilities.</p>
                                <p>Present in Romania since 2008, Bandai Namco Entertainment Romania – part of the international group Bandai Namco Holdings – develops games on mobile platforms, such as smartphones and tablets.</p>
                                <p>In 2017, Bandai Namco Entertainment Romania initiated the expansion of game development capabilities to other platforms such as the latest generation PCs and PCs. The company is known for developing games such as Pac-Man, Digimon Heroes!, Pac-Man Championship Edition DX, Sword Art Online: Hollow Fragment.</p>
                                <div id="tw-target-text-container"><span lang="en">”One priority for me was to prepare the land for a relocation of Bandai Namco Entertainment Romania in a suitable place to continue the upward trend of the company. We also wanted to meet the team’s expectations, in line with the trends of the latest generation workspaces. The evolution of Pac-Man, started almost 40 years ago, and will continue to enjoy millions of users around the world. The location we selected corresponds to the company’s strategy of development by recruiting young talents, young people passionate about new gaming technologies,&nbsp; ”&nbsp;</span><span lang="en">Cristian Dragomir, COO Bandai Namco Entertainment Romania, stated.</span><span lang="en">Starting January 2019, the company will relocate its operations to its new headquarters, completing the list of IT players present in the West Midlands office area.&nbsp;</span><span lang="en">”Bandai Namco’s relocation to Orhideea Towers confirms the growing trend of technology companies and the fact that these organizations are preparing for new generations of employees. It is the third time in a year when we were working for a Japanese company – the selection process was rigorous and the result – a confirmation of a well-balanced decision: a quality building with premium facilities and compact space on a single level, ” explained Andreea Paun, managing partner Griffes, who coordinated the rental process</span>In Romania, CA Immo has been present since 2001 and has a portfolio of five office buildings: Opera Center 1 and 2, River Place, Europe House and Bucharest Business Park, totaling a leasable area of &#8203;&#8203;about 106,300 square meters, a rate occupancy of 93 percent and a value of 258 million euros.</div>
                                <a class="cfs-hyperlink" href="https://www.wall-street.ro/articol/Real-Estate/215805/griffes-andreea-paun-a-mutat-preturi-pentru-tine-in-city-offices.html" target="_blank" tabindex="0"><span class="text">Source</span></a>                                
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
