                    <div class="col-8 medium-12">
                        <div class="slider-content">
                            <h3>RedBull moves to Unirii View </h3>
                            <div class="date">March 5, 2018  </div>
                            <div class="text-scroll mCustomScrollbar">
                                <p>Red Bull Romania leased 600 square meters of office space in Unirii View and will establish its local office in the tallest modern office building in downtown Bucharest.</p>
                                <p>Unirii View is located on Corneliu Coposu Boulevard, only five-minute walk from Unirii Square, and will have 19 floors, including ground floor, 17 office floors plus a mechanical last floor and an underground parking, divided into three levels.</p>
                                <p>The construction of the project, due to be delivered in the summer of 2018, is advancing rapidly, now being undertaken works at the 14th level. The project will have a total gross leasable area of 17,500 square meters and with a height that will reach 73 meters will be the most visible building in downtown Bucharest.&nbsp;</p>
                                <p>“Unirii View and the downtown area continues to attract main headquarters, a normal fact taking into account the needs of companies looking for excellent visibility and good connections for their employees and we will see in the near future more companies taking the same decision”, said Andreea Paun, managing partner of real estate consultant Griffes, in charge with leasing strategy and commercial management for the project.</p>
